properties.Name: E.B. Bain Water Treatment Plant
properties.description: Looks extremely hard to get in but well worth the effort. Beautiful art deco style on the interior. Has a barbed wire fence with no holes as far as I can tell + motion sensors and possibly cameras as well.

properties.Name: St. Agnes Hospital ruins
properties.description: Very tame, open brick ruins, just hop over the fence. Best at night, bring a good camera for a beautiful long exposure.

properties.Name: Rockingham Mill Foundation
properties.description: Best in summer, but impossible to explore then because of kudzu

properties.Name: Rumored entrance to Cameron Village Underground
Partially abandoned mill
properties.description: There is an active landscaping supply building at the bottom of the property. Exploring any part of the property is extremely risky.

properties.Name: Abandoned farm
properties.description: Watch out for the property owners

properties.Name: Old Linden School
properties.description: Watch out for holes in the floor

properties.Name: Rock Hill Printing and Finishing Company
Castle Mont Rouge
properties.description: Fenced off with possibly hostile property owners

properties.Name: Medical Building
properties.description: Locked, no tree cover, and brightly lit at night. This place would be impossible to get in without being highly visible.

properties.Name: Burlington Industries plant
properties.description: Massive and fairly cool, but fairly blown out. Hard to navigate between buildings because of insane overgrowth. WATCH FOR ASBESTOS CEILING TILES.

properties.Name: Atlantic Coast Line Railway Emerson Shops
RMS Queen Mary and Russian Submarine
Possible plant remains + super dense forest
Signal Hill
properties.description: Good view of city, especially at night. Bring a machete, as you may need to clear brush to get a full view without climbing tower. Cell tower is not transmitting (pretty sure) and climbable but you could be caught, even at night. Don't use lights, and squeeze through gap in fence.

properties.Name: Partially collapsed manufacturer
properties.description: Very close / part of active road construction company. Visit in summer to retain treecover.

properties.Name: Olmos Dam
properties.description: Behind the dam has lots of graffiti and you can climb into the flood control gates at your own risk

properties.Name: Peters mountain installation
properties.description: Possible COG, part of the tropospheric relay system

properties.Name: Abandoned mill
properties.description: Pretty cleared out, flooded basement. Not much to see but pretty cool at night.
